94static krb5_error_code
95pk_check_pkauthenticator_win2k(krb5_context context,
96 PKAuthenticator_Win2k *a,
97 const KDC_REQ *req)
98{
99 krb5_timestamp now;
100
101 krb5_timeofday (context, &now);
102
103 /* XXX cusec */
104 if (a->ctime == 0 || labs(a->ctime - now) > context->max_skew) {
105 krb5_clear_error_message(context);
106 return KRB5KRB_AP_ERR_SKEW;
107 }
108 return 0;
109}
110
111static krb5_error_code
112pk_check_pkauthenticator(krb5_context context,
113 PKAuthenticator *a,
114 const KDC_REQ *req)
115{
116 u_char *buf = NULL;
117 size_t buf_size;
118 krb5_error_code ret;
119 size_t len = 0;
120 krb5_timestamp now;
121 Checksum checksum;
122
123 krb5_timeofday (context, &now);
124
125 /* XXX cusec */
126 if (a->ctime == 0 || labs(a->ctime - now) > context->max_skew) {
127 krb5_clear_error_message(context);
128 return KRB5KRB_AP_ERR_SKEW;
129 }
130
131 ASN1_MALLOC_ENCODE(KDC_REQ_BODY, buf, buf_size, &req->req_body, &len, ret);
132 if (ret) {
133 krb5_clear_error_message(context);
134 return ret;
135 }
136 if (buf_size != len)
137 krb5_abortx(context, "Internal error in ASN.1 encoder");
138
139 ret = krb5_create_checksum(context,
140 NULL,
141 0,
142 CKSUMTYPE_SHA1,
143 buf,
144 len,
145 &checksum);
146 free(buf);
147 if (ret) {
148 krb5_clear_error_message(context);
149 return ret;
150 }
151
152 if (a->paChecksum == NULL) {
153 krb5_clear_error_message(context);
154 ret = KRB5_KDC_ERR_PA_CHECKSUM_MUST_BE_INCLUDED;
155 goto out;
156 }
157
158 if (der_heim_octet_string_cmp(a->paChecksum, &checksum.checksum) != 0) {
159 krb5_clear_error_message(context);
160 ret = KRB5KRB_ERR_GENERIC;
161 }
162
163out:
164 free_Checksum(&checksum);
165
166 return ret;
167}

169void
170_kdc_pk_free_client_param(krb5_context context, pk_client_params *cp)
171{
172 if (cp == NULL)
173 return;
174 if (cp->cert)
175 hx509_cert_free(cp->cert);
176 if (cp->verify_ctx)
177 hx509_verify_destroy_ctx(cp->verify_ctx);
178 if (cp->keyex == USE_DH) {
179 if (cp->u.dh.key)
180 DH_free(cp->u.dh.key);
181 if (cp->u.dh.public_key)
182 BN_free(cp->u.dh.public_key);
183 }
184 if (cp->keyex == USE_ECDH)
185 _kdc_pk_free_client_ec_param(context, cp->u.ecdh.key,
186 cp->u.ecdh.public_key);
187 krb5_free_keyblock_contents(context, &cp->reply_key);
188 if (cp->dh_group_name)
189 free(cp->dh_group_name);
190 if (cp->peer)
191 hx509_peer_info_free(cp->peer);
192 if (cp->client_anchors)
193 hx509_certs_free(&cp->client_anchors);
194 memset(cp, 0, sizeof(*cp));
195 free(cp);
196}

198static krb5_error_code
199generate_dh_keyblock(krb5_context context,
200 pk_client_params *client_params,
201 krb5_enctype enctype)
202{
203 unsigned char *dh_gen_key = NULL;
204 krb5_keyblock key;
205 krb5_error_code ret;
206 size_t dh_gen_keylen, size;
207
208 memset(&key, 0, sizeof(key));
209
210 if (client_params->keyex == USE_DH) {
211
212 if (client_params->u.dh.public_key == NULL) {
213 ret = KRB5KRB_ERR_GENERIC;
214 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret, "missing DH public_key");
215 goto out;
216 }
217
218 if (!DH_generate_key(client_params->u.dh.key)) {
219 ret = KRB5KRB_ERR_GENERIC;
220 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret,
221 "Can't generate Diffie-Hellman keys");
222 goto out;
223 }
224
225 size = DH_size(client_params->u.dh.key);
226
227 dh_gen_key = malloc(size);
228 if (dh_gen_key == NULL) {
229 ret = ENOMEM;
230 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret, "malloc: out of memory");
231 goto out;
232 }
233
234 dh_gen_keylen = DH_compute_key(dh_gen_key,client_params->u.dh.public_key, client_params->u.dh.key);
235 if (dh_gen_keylen == (size_t)-1) {
236 ret = KRB5KRB_ERR_GENERIC;
237 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret,
238 "Can't compute Diffie-Hellman key");
239 goto out;
240 }
241 if (dh_gen_keylen < size) {
242 size -= dh_gen_keylen;
243 memmove(dh_gen_key + size, dh_gen_key, dh_gen_keylen);
244 memset(dh_gen_key, 0, size);
245 }
246
247 ret = 0;
248 } else if (client_params->keyex == USE_ECDH) {
249 if (client_params->u.ecdh.public_key == NULL) {
250 ret = KRB5KRB_ERR_GENERIC;
251 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret, "missing ECDH public_key");
252 goto out;
253 }
254 ret = _kdc_generate_ecdh_keyblock(context,
255 client_params->u.ecdh.public_key,
256 &client_params->u.ecdh.key,
257 &dh_gen_key, &dh_gen_keylen);
258 if (ret)
259 goto out;
260 } else {
261 ret = KRB5KRB_ERR_GENERIC;
262 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret,
263 "Diffie-Hellman not selected keys");
264 goto out;
265 }
266
267 ret = _krb5_pk_octetstring2key(context,
268 enctype,
269 dh_gen_key, dh_gen_keylen,
270 NULL, NULL,
271 &client_params->reply_key);
272
273 out:
274 if (dh_gen_key)
275 free(dh_gen_key);
276 if (key.keyvalue.data)
277 krb5_free_keyblock_contents(context, &key);
278
279 return ret;
280}

282static BIGNUM *
283integer_to_BN(krb5_context context, const char *field, heim_integer *f)
284{
285 BIGNUM *bn;
286
287 bn = BN_bin2bn((const unsigned char *)f->data, f->length, NULL);
288 if (bn == NULL) {
289 krb5_set_error_message(context, KRB5_BADMSGTYPE,
290 "PKINIT: parsing BN failed %s", field);
291 return NULL;
292 }
293 BN_set_negative(bn, f->negative);
294 return bn;
295}

297static krb5_error_code
298get_dh_param(krb5_context context,
299 krb5_kdc_configuration *config,
300 SubjectPublicKeyInfo *dh_key_info,
301 pk_client_params *client_params)
302{
303 DomainParameters dhparam;
304 DH *dh = NULL;
305 krb5_error_code ret;
306
307 memset(&dhparam, 0, sizeof(dhparam));
308
309 if ((dh_key_info->subjectPublicKey.length % 8) != 0) {
310 ret = KRB5_BADMSGTYPE;
311 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret,
312 "PKINIT: subjectPublicKey not aligned "
313 "to 8 bit boundary");
314 goto out;
315 }
316
317 if (dh_key_info->algorithm.parameters == NULL) {
318 krb5_set_error_message(context, KRB5_BADMSGTYPE,
319 "PKINIT missing algorithm parameter "
320 "in clientPublicValue");
321 return KRB5_BADMSGTYPE;
322 }
323
324 ret = decode_DomainParameters(dh_key_info->algorithm.parameters->data,
325 dh_key_info->algorithm.parameters->length,
326 &dhparam,
327 NULL);
328 if (ret) {
329 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret, "Can't decode algorithm "
330 "parameters in clientPublicValue");
331 goto out;
332 }
333
334 ret = _krb5_dh_group_ok(context, config->pkinit_dh_min_bits,
335 &dhparam.p, &dhparam.g, dhparam.q, moduli,
336 &client_params->dh_group_name);
337 if (ret) {
338 /* XXX send back proposal of better group */
339 goto out;
340 }
341
342 dh = DH_new();
343 if (dh == NULL) {
344 ret = ENOMEM;
345 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret, "Cannot create DH structure");
346 goto out;
347 }
348 ret = KRB5_BADMSGTYPE;
349 BIGNUM *p, *q, *g;
350 p = integer_to_BN(context, "DH prime", &dhparam.p);
351 if (p == NULL)
352 goto out;
353 g = integer_to_BN(context, "DH base", &dhparam.g);
354 if (g == NULL)
355 goto out;
356
357 if (dhparam.q) {
358 q = integer_to_BN(context, "DH p-1 factor", dhparam.q);
359 if (q == NULL)
360 goto out;
361 } else
362 q = NULL;
363
364#if OPENSSL_VERSION_NUMBER < 0x10100000UL
365 dh->p = p;
366 if (q)
367 dh->q = q;
368 dh->g = g;
369#else
370 DH_set0_pqg(dh, p, q, g);
371#endif
372 {
373 heim_integer glue;
374 size_t size;
375
376 ret = decode_DHPublicKey(dh_key_info->subjectPublicKey.data,
377 dh_key_info->subjectPublicKey.length / 8,
378 &glue,
379 &size);
380 if (ret) {
381 krb5_clear_error_message(context);
382 return ret;
383 }
384
385 client_params->u.dh.public_key = integer_to_BN(context,
386 "subjectPublicKey",
387 &glue);
388 der_free_heim_integer(&glue);
389 if (client_params->u.dh.public_key == NULL) {
390 ret = KRB5_BADMSGTYPE;
391 goto out;
392 }
393 }
394
395 client_params->u.dh.key = dh;
396 dh = NULL;
397 ret = 0;
398
399 out:
400 if (dh)
401 DH_free(dh);
402 free_DomainParameters(&dhparam);
403 return ret;
404}

406krb5_error_code
407_kdc_pk_rd_padata(krb5_context context,
408 krb5_kdc_configuration *config,
409 const KDC_REQ *req,
410 const PA_DATA *pa,
411 hdb_entry_ex *client,
412 pk_client_params **ret_params)
413{
414 pk_client_params *cp;
415 krb5_error_code ret;
416 heim_oid eContentType = { 0, NULL }, contentInfoOid = { 0, NULL };
417 krb5_data eContent = { 0, NULL };
418 krb5_data signed_content = { 0, NULL };
419 const char *type = "unknown type";
420 hx509_certs trust_anchors;
421 int have_data = 0;
422 const HDB_Ext_PKINIT_cert *pc;
423
424 *ret_params = NULL;
425
426 if (!config->enable_pkinit) {
427 kdc_log(context, config, 0, "PK-INIT request but PK-INIT not enabled");
428 krb5_clear_error_message(context);
429 return 0;
430 }
431
432 cp = calloc(1, sizeof(*cp));
433 if (cp == NULL) {
434 krb5_clear_error_message(context);
435 ret = ENOMEM;
436 goto out;
437 }
438
439 ret = hx509_certs_init(context->hx509ctx,
440 "MEMORY:trust-anchors",
441 0, NULL, &trust_anchors);
442 if (ret) {
443 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret, "failed to create trust anchors");
444 goto out;
445 }
446
447 ret = hx509_certs_merge(context->hx509ctx, trust_anchors,
448 kdc_identity->anchors);
449 if (ret) {
450 hx509_certs_free(&trust_anchors);
451 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret, "failed to create verify context");
452 goto out;
453 }
454
455 /* Add any registered certificates for this client as trust anchors */
456 ret = hdb_entry_get_pkinit_cert(&client->entry, &pc);
457 if (ret == 0 && pc != NULL) {
458 hx509_cert cert;
459 unsigned int i;
460
461 for (i = 0; i < pc->len; i++) {
462 cert = hx509_cert_init_data(context->hx509ctx,
463 pc->val[i].cert.data,
464 pc->val[i].cert.length,
465 NULL);
466 if (cert == NULL)
467 continue;
468 hx509_certs_add(context->hx509ctx, trust_anchors, cert);
469 hx509_cert_free(cert);
470 }
471 }
472
473 ret = hx509_verify_init_ctx(context->hx509ctx, &cp->verify_ctx);
474 if (ret) {
475 hx509_certs_free(&trust_anchors);
476 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret, "failed to create verify context");
477 goto out;
478 }
479
480 hx509_verify_set_time(cp->verify_ctx, kdc_time);
481 hx509_verify_attach_anchors(cp->verify_ctx, trust_anchors);
482 hx509_certs_free(&trust_anchors);
483
484 if (config->pkinit_allow_proxy_certs)
485 hx509_verify_set_proxy_certificate(cp->verify_ctx, 1);
486
487 if (pa->padata_type == KRB5_PADATA_PK_AS_REQ_WIN) {
488 PA_PK_AS_REQ_Win2k r;
489
490 type = "PK-INIT-Win2k";
491
492 if (_kdc_is_anon_request(&req->req_body)) {
493 ret = KRB5_KDC_ERR_PUBLIC_KEY_ENCRYPTION_NOT_SUPPORTED;
494 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret,
495 "Anon not supported in RSA mode");
496 goto out;
497 }
498
499 ret = decode_PA_PK_AS_REQ_Win2k(pa->padata_value.data,
500 pa->padata_value.length,
501 &r,
502 NULL);
503 if (ret) {
504 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret, "Can't decode "
505 "PK-AS-REQ-Win2k: %d", ret);
506 goto out;
507 }
508
509 ret = hx509_cms_unwrap_ContentInfo(&r.signed_auth_pack,
510 &contentInfoOid,
511 &signed_content,
512 &have_data);
513 free_PA_PK_AS_REQ_Win2k(&r);
514 if (ret) {
515 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret,
516 "Can't unwrap ContentInfo(win): %d", ret);
517 goto out;
518 }
519
520 } else if (pa->padata_type == KRB5_PADATA_PK_AS_REQ) {
521 PA_PK_AS_REQ r;
522
523 type = "PK-INIT-IETF";
524
525 ret = decode_PA_PK_AS_REQ(pa->padata_value.data,
526 pa->padata_value.length,
527 &r,
528 NULL);
529 if (ret) {
530 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret,
531 "Can't decode PK-AS-REQ: %d", ret);
532 goto out;
533 }
534
535 /* XXX look at r.kdcPkId */
536 if (r.trustedCertifiers) {
537 ExternalPrincipalIdentifiers *edi = r.trustedCertifiers;
538 unsigned int i, maxedi;
539
540 ret = hx509_certs_init(context->hx509ctx,
541 "MEMORY:client-anchors",
542 0, NULL,
543 &cp->client_anchors);
544 if (ret) {
545 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret,
546 "Can't allocate client anchors: %d",
547 ret);
548 goto out;
549
550 }
551 /*
552 * If the client sent more then 10 EDI, don't bother
553 * looking more then 10 of performance reasons.
554 */
555 maxedi = edi->len;
556 if (maxedi > 10)
557 maxedi = 10;
558 for (i = 0; i < maxedi; i++) {
559 IssuerAndSerialNumber iasn;
560 hx509_query *q;
561 hx509_cert cert;
562 size_t size;
563
564 if (edi->val[i].issuerAndSerialNumber == NULL)
565 continue;
566
567 ret = hx509_query_alloc(context->hx509ctx, &q);
568 if (ret) {
569 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret,
570 "Failed to allocate hx509_query");
571 goto out;
572 }
573
574 ret = decode_IssuerAndSerialNumber(edi->val[i].issuerAndSerialNumber->data,
575 edi->val[i].issuerAndSerialNumber->length,
576 &iasn,
577 &size);
578 if (ret) {
579 hx509_query_free(context->hx509ctx, q);
580 continue;
581 }
582 ret = hx509_query_match_issuer_serial(q, &iasn.issuer, &iasn.serialNumber);
583 free_IssuerAndSerialNumber(&iasn);
584 if (ret) {
585 hx509_query_free(context->hx509ctx, q);
586 continue;
587 }
588
589 ret = hx509_certs_find(context->hx509ctx,
590 kdc_identity->certs,
591 q,
592 &cert);
593 hx509_query_free(context->hx509ctx, q);
594 if (ret)
595 continue;
596 hx509_certs_add(context->hx509ctx,
597 cp->client_anchors, cert);
598 hx509_cert_free(cert);
599 }
600 }
601
602 ret = hx509_cms_unwrap_ContentInfo(&r.signedAuthPack,
603 &contentInfoOid,
604 &signed_content,
605 &have_data);
606 free_PA_PK_AS_REQ(&r);
607 if (ret) {
608 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret,
609 "Can't unwrap ContentInfo: %d", ret);
610 goto out;
611 }
612
613 } else {
614 krb5_clear_error_message(context);
615 ret = KRB5KDC_ERR_PADATA_TYPE_NOSUPP;
616 goto out;
617 }
618
619 ret = der_heim_oid_cmp(&contentInfoOid, &asn1_oid_id_pkcs7_signedData);
620 if (ret != 0) {
621 ret = KRB5KRB_ERR_GENERIC;
622 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret,
623 "PK-AS-REQ-Win2k invalid content type oid");
624 goto out;
625 }
626
627 if (!have_data) {
628 ret = KRB5KRB_ERR_GENERIC;
629 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret,
630 "PK-AS-REQ-Win2k no signed auth pack");
631 goto out;
632 }
633
634 {
635 hx509_certs signer_certs;
636 int flags = HX509_CMS_VS_ALLOW_DATA_OID_MISMATCH; /* BTMM */
637
638 if (_kdc_is_anon_request(&req->req_body))
639 flags |= HX509_CMS_VS_ALLOW_ZERO_SIGNER;
640
641 ret = hx509_cms_verify_signed(context->hx509ctx,
642 cp->verify_ctx,
643 flags,
644 signed_content.data,
645 signed_content.length,
646 NULL,
647 kdc_identity->certpool,
648 &eContentType,
649 &eContent,
650 &signer_certs);
651 if (ret) {
652 char *s = hx509_get_error_string(context->hx509ctx, ret);
653 krb5_warnx(context, "PKINIT: failed to verify signature: %s: %d",
654 s, ret);
655 free(s);
656 goto out;
657 }
658
659 if (signer_certs) {
660 ret = hx509_get_one_cert(context->hx509ctx, signer_certs,
661 &cp->cert);
662 hx509_certs_free(&signer_certs);
663 }
664 if (ret)
665 goto out;
666 }
667
668 /* Signature is correct, now verify the signed message */
669 if (der_heim_oid_cmp(&eContentType, &asn1_oid_id_pkcs7_data) != 0 &&
670 der_heim_oid_cmp(&eContentType, &asn1_oid_id_pkauthdata) != 0)
671 {
672 ret = KRB5_BADMSGTYPE;
673 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret, "got wrong oid for pkauthdata");
674 goto out;
675 }
676
677 if (pa->padata_type == KRB5_PADATA_PK_AS_REQ_WIN) {
678 AuthPack_Win2k ap;
679
680 ret = decode_AuthPack_Win2k(eContent.data,
681 eContent.length,
682 &ap,
683 NULL);
684 if (ret) {
685 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret,
686 "Can't decode AuthPack: %d", ret);
687 goto out;
688 }
689
690 ret = pk_check_pkauthenticator_win2k(context,
691 &ap.pkAuthenticator,
692 req);
693 if (ret) {
694 free_AuthPack_Win2k(&ap);
695 goto out;
696 }
697
698 cp->type = PKINIT_WIN2K;
699 cp->nonce = ap.pkAuthenticator.nonce;
700
701 if (ap.clientPublicValue) {
702 ret = KRB5KRB_ERR_GENERIC;
703 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret,
704 "DH not supported for windows");
705 goto out;
706 }
707 free_AuthPack_Win2k(&ap);
708
709 } else if (pa->padata_type == KRB5_PADATA_PK_AS_REQ) {
710 AuthPack ap;
711
712 ret = decode_AuthPack(eContent.data,
713 eContent.length,
714 &ap,
715 NULL);
716 if (ret) {
717 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret,
718 "Can't decode AuthPack: %d", ret);
719 free_AuthPack(&ap);
720 goto out;
721 }
722
723 if (_kdc_is_anon_request(&req->req_body) &&
724 ap.clientPublicValue == NULL) {
725 free_AuthPack(&ap);
726 ret = KRB5_KDC_ERR_PUBLIC_KEY_ENCRYPTION_NOT_SUPPORTED;
727 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret,
728 "Anon not supported in RSA mode");
729 goto out;
730 }
731
732 ret = pk_check_pkauthenticator(context,
733 &ap.pkAuthenticator,
734 req);
735 if (ret) {
736 free_AuthPack(&ap);
737 goto out;
738 }
739
740 cp->type = PKINIT_27;
741 cp->nonce = ap.pkAuthenticator.nonce;
742
743 if (ap.clientPublicValue) {
744 if (der_heim_oid_cmp(&ap.clientPublicValue->algorithm.algorithm, &asn1_oid_id_dhpublicnumber) == 0) {
745 cp->keyex = USE_DH;
746 ret = get_dh_param(context, config,
747 ap.clientPublicValue, cp);
748 } else if (der_heim_oid_cmp(&ap.clientPublicValue->algorithm.algorithm, &asn1_oid_id_ecPublicKey) == 0) {
749 cp->keyex = USE_ECDH;
750 ret = _kdc_get_ecdh_param(context, config,
751 ap.clientPublicValue,
752 &cp->u.ecdh.public_key);
753 } else {
754 ret = KRB5_BADMSGTYPE;
755 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret, "PKINIT unknown DH mechanism");
756 }
757 if (ret) {
758 free_AuthPack(&ap);
759 goto out;
760 }
761 } else
762 cp->keyex = USE_RSA;
763
764 ret = hx509_peer_info_alloc(context->hx509ctx,
765 &cp->peer);
766 if (ret) {
767 free_AuthPack(&ap);
768 goto out;
769 }
770
771 if (ap.supportedCMSTypes) {
772 ret = hx509_peer_info_set_cms_algs(context->hx509ctx,
773 cp->peer,
774 ap.supportedCMSTypes->val,
775 ap.supportedCMSTypes->len);
776 if (ret) {
777 free_AuthPack(&ap);
778 goto out;
779 }
780 } else {
781 /* assume old client */
782 hx509_peer_info_add_cms_alg(context->hx509ctx, cp->peer,
783 hx509_crypto_des_rsdi_ede3_cbc());
784 hx509_peer_info_add_cms_alg(context->hx509ctx, cp->peer,
785 hx509_signature_rsa_with_sha1());
786 hx509_peer_info_add_cms_alg(context->hx509ctx, cp->peer,
787 hx509_signature_sha1());
788 }
789 free_AuthPack(&ap);
790 } else
791 krb5_abortx(context, "internal pkinit error");
792
793 kdc_log(context, config, 0, "PK-INIT request of type %s", type);
794
795out:
796 if (ret)
797 krb5_warn(context, ret, "PKINIT");
798
799 if (signed_content.data)
800 free(signed_content.data);
801 krb5_data_free(&eContent);
802 der_free_oid(&eContentType);
803 der_free_oid(&contentInfoOid);
804 if (ret) {
805 _kdc_pk_free_client_param(context, cp);
806 } else
807 *ret_params = cp;
808 return ret;
809}

815static krb5_error_code
816BN_to_integer(krb5_context context, const BIGNUM *bn, heim_integer *integer)
817{
818 integer->length = BN_num_bytes(bn);
819 integer->data = malloc(integer->length);
820 if (integer->data == NULL) {
821 krb5_clear_error_message(context);
822 return ENOMEM;
823 }
824 BN_bn2bin(bn, integer->data);
825 integer->negative = BN_is_negative(bn);
826 return 0;
827}
828
829static krb5_error_code
830pk_mk_pa_reply_enckey(krb5_context context,
831 krb5_kdc_configuration *config,
832 pk_client_params *cp,
833 const KDC_REQ *req,
834 const krb5_data *req_buffer,
835 krb5_keyblock *reply_key,
836 ContentInfo *content_info,
837 hx509_cert *kdc_cert)
838{
839 const heim_oid *envelopedAlg = NULL, *sdAlg = NULL, *evAlg = NULL;
840 krb5_error_code ret;
841 krb5_data buf, signed_data;
842 size_t size = 0;
843 int do_win2k = 0;
844
845 krb5_data_zero(&buf);
846 krb5_data_zero(&signed_data);
847
848 *kdc_cert = NULL;
849
850 /*
851 * If the message client is a win2k-type but it send pa data
852 * 09-binding it expects a IETF (checksum) reply so there can be
853 * no replay attacks.
854 */
855
856 switch (cp->type) {
857 case PKINIT_WIN2K: {
858 int i = 0;
859 if (_kdc_find_padata(req, &i, KRB5_PADATA_PK_AS_09_BINDING) == NULL
860 && config->pkinit_require_binding == 0)
861 {
862 do_win2k = 1;
863 }
864 sdAlg = &asn1_oid_id_pkcs7_data;
865 evAlg = &asn1_oid_id_pkcs7_data;
866 envelopedAlg = &asn1_oid_id_rsadsi_des_ede3_cbc;
867 break;
868 }
869 case PKINIT_27:
870 sdAlg = &asn1_oid_id_pkrkeydata;
871 evAlg = &asn1_oid_id_pkcs7_signedData;
872 break;
873 default:
874 krb5_abortx(context, "internal pkinit error");
875 }
876
877 if (do_win2k) {
878 ReplyKeyPack_Win2k kp;
879 memset(&kp, 0, sizeof(kp));
880
881 ret = copy_EncryptionKey(reply_key, &kp.replyKey);
882 if (ret) {
883 krb5_clear_error_message(context);
884 goto out;
885 }
886 kp.nonce = cp->nonce;
887
888 ASN1_MALLOC_ENCODE(ReplyKeyPack_Win2k,
889 buf.data, buf.length,
890 &kp, &size,ret);
891 free_ReplyKeyPack_Win2k(&kp);
892 } else {
893 krb5_crypto ascrypto;
894 ReplyKeyPack kp;
895 memset(&kp, 0, sizeof(kp));
896
897 ret = copy_EncryptionKey(reply_key, &kp.replyKey);
898 if (ret) {
899 krb5_clear_error_message(context);
900 goto out;
901 }
902
903 ret = krb5_crypto_init(context, reply_key, 0, &ascrypto);
904 if (ret) {
905 krb5_clear_error_message(context);
906 goto out;
907 }
908
909 ret = krb5_create_checksum(context, ascrypto, 6, 0,
910 req_buffer->data, req_buffer->length,
911 &kp.asChecksum);
912 if (ret) {
913 krb5_clear_error_message(context);
914 goto out;
915 }
916
917 ret = krb5_crypto_destroy(context, ascrypto);
918 if (ret) {
919 krb5_clear_error_message(context);
920 goto out;
921 }
922 ASN1_MALLOC_ENCODE(ReplyKeyPack, buf.data, buf.length, &kp, &size,ret);
923 free_ReplyKeyPack(&kp);
924 }
925 if (ret) {
926 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret, "ASN.1 encoding of ReplyKeyPack "
927 "failed (%d)", ret);
928 goto out;
929 }
930 if (buf.length != size)
931 krb5_abortx(context, "Internal ASN.1 encoder error");
932
933 {
934 hx509_query *q;
935 hx509_cert cert;
936
937 ret = hx509_query_alloc(context->hx509ctx, &q);
938 if (ret)
939 goto out;
940
941 hx509_query_match_option(q, HX509_QUERY_OPTION_PRIVATE_KEY);
942 if (config->pkinit_kdc_friendly_name)
943 hx509_query_match_friendly_name(q, config->pkinit_kdc_friendly_name);
944
945 ret = hx509_certs_find(context->hx509ctx,
946 kdc_identity->certs,
947 q,
948 &cert);
949 hx509_query_free(context->hx509ctx, q);
950 if (ret)
951 goto out;
952
953 ret = hx509_cms_create_signed_1(context->hx509ctx,
954 0,
955 sdAlg,
956 buf.data,
957 buf.length,
958 NULL,
959 cert,
960 cp->peer,
961 cp->client_anchors,
962 kdc_identity->certpool,
963 &signed_data);
964 *kdc_cert = cert;
965 }
966
967 krb5_data_free(&buf);
968 if (ret)
969 goto out;
970
971 if (cp->type == PKINIT_WIN2K) {
972 ret = hx509_cms_wrap_ContentInfo(&asn1_oid_id_pkcs7_signedData,
973 &signed_data,
974 &buf);
975 if (ret)
976 goto out;
977 krb5_data_free(&signed_data);
978 signed_data = buf;
979 }
980
981 ret = hx509_cms_envelope_1(context->hx509ctx,
982 HX509_CMS_EV_NO_KU_CHECK,
983 cp->cert,
984 signed_data.data, signed_data.length,
985 envelopedAlg,
986 evAlg, &buf);
987 if (ret)
988 goto out;
989
990 ret = _krb5_pk_mk_ContentInfo(context,
991 &buf,
992 &asn1_oid_id_pkcs7_envelopedData,
993 content_info);
994out:
995 if (ret && *kdc_cert) {
996 hx509_cert_free(*kdc_cert);
997 *kdc_cert = NULL;
998 }
999
1000 krb5_data_free(&buf);
1001 krb5_data_free(&signed_data);
1002 return ret;
1003}

1005/*
1006 *
1007 */
1008
1009static krb5_error_code
1010pk_mk_pa_reply_dh(krb5_context context,
1011 krb5_kdc_configuration *config,
1012 pk_client_params *cp,
1013 ContentInfo *content_info,
1014 hx509_cert *kdc_cert)
1015{
1016 KDCDHKeyInfo dh_info;
1017 krb5_data signed_data, buf;
1018 ContentInfo contentinfo;
1019 krb5_error_code ret;
1020 hx509_cert cert;
1021 hx509_query *q;
1022 size_t size = 0;
1023
1024 memset(&contentinfo, 0, sizeof(contentinfo));
1025 memset(&dh_info, 0, sizeof(dh_info));
1026 krb5_data_zero(&signed_data);
1027 krb5_data_zero(&buf);
1028
1029 *kdc_cert = NULL;
1030
1031 if (cp->keyex == USE_DH) {
1032 DH *kdc_dh = cp->u.dh.key;
1033 heim_integer i;
1034
1035 const BIGNUM *pub_key;
1036#if OPENSSL_VERSION_NUMBER < 0x10100000UL
1037 pub_key = kdc_dh->pub_key;
1038#else
1039 DH_get0_key(kdc_dh, &pub_key, NULL);
1040#endif
1041 ret = BN_to_integer(context, pub_key, &i);
1042 if (ret)
1043 return ret;
1044
1045 ASN1_MALLOC_ENCODE(DHPublicKey, buf.data, buf.length, &i, &size, ret);
1046 der_free_heim_integer(&i);
1047 if (ret) {
1048 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret, "ASN.1 encoding of "
1049 "DHPublicKey failed (%d)", ret);
1050 return ret;
1051 }
1052 if (buf.length != size)
1053 krb5_abortx(context, "Internal ASN.1 encoder error");
1054
1055 dh_info.subjectPublicKey.length = buf.length * 8;
1056 dh_info.subjectPublicKey.data = buf.data;
1057 krb5_data_zero(&buf);
1058 } else if (cp->keyex == USE_ECDH) {
1059 unsigned char *p;
1060 ret = _kdc_serialize_ecdh_key(context, cp->u.ecdh.key, &p,
1061 &dh_info.subjectPublicKey.length);
1062 dh_info.subjectPublicKey.data = p;
1063 if (ret)
1064 goto out;
1065 } else
1066 krb5_abortx(context, "no keyex selected ?");
1067
1068
1069 dh_info.nonce = cp->nonce;
1070
1071 ASN1_MALLOC_ENCODE(KDCDHKeyInfo, buf.data, buf.length, &dh_info, &size,
1072 ret);
1073 if (ret) {
1074 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret, "ASN.1 encoding of "
1075 "KdcDHKeyInfo failed (%d)", ret);
1076 goto out;
1077 }
1078 if (buf.length != size)
1079 krb5_abortx(context, "Internal ASN.1 encoder error");
1080
1081 /*
1082 * Create the SignedData structure and sign the KdcDHKeyInfo
1083 * filled in above
1084 */
1085
1086 ret = hx509_query_alloc(context->hx509ctx, &q);
1087 if (ret)
1088 goto out;
1089
1090 hx509_query_match_option(q, HX509_QUERY_OPTION_PRIVATE_KEY);
1091 if (config->pkinit_kdc_friendly_name)
1092 hx509_query_match_friendly_name(q, config->pkinit_kdc_friendly_name);
1093
1094 ret = hx509_certs_find(context->hx509ctx,
1095 kdc_identity->certs,
1096 q,
1097 &cert);
1098 hx509_query_free(context->hx509ctx, q);
1099 if (ret)
1100 goto out;
1101
1102 ret = hx509_cms_create_signed_1(context->hx509ctx,
1103 0,
1104 &asn1_oid_id_pkdhkeydata,
1105 buf.data,
1106 buf.length,
1107 NULL,
1108 cert,
1109 cp->peer,
1110 cp->client_anchors,
1111 kdc_identity->certpool,
1112 &signed_data);
1113 if (ret) {
1114 kdc_log(context, config, 0, "Failed signing the DH* reply: %d", ret);
1115 goto out;
1116 }
1117 *kdc_cert = cert;
1118
1119 ret = _krb5_pk_mk_ContentInfo(context,
1120 &signed_data,
1121 &asn1_oid_id_pkcs7_signedData,
1122 content_info);
1123 if (ret)
1124 goto out;
1125
1126 out:
1127 if (ret && *kdc_cert) {
1128 hx509_cert_free(*kdc_cert);
1129 *kdc_cert = NULL;
1130 }
1131
1132 krb5_data_free(&buf);
1133 krb5_data_free(&signed_data);
1134 free_KDCDHKeyInfo(&dh_info);
1135
1136 return ret;
1137}

1139/*
1140 *
1141 */
1142
1143krb5_error_code
1144_kdc_pk_mk_pa_reply(krb5_context context,
1145 krb5_kdc_configuration *config,
1146 pk_client_params *cp,
1147 const hdb_entry_ex *client,
1148 krb5_enctype sessionetype,
1149 const KDC_REQ *req,
1150 const krb5_data *req_buffer,
1151 krb5_keyblock *reply_key,
1152 krb5_keyblock *sessionkey,
1153 METHOD_DATA *md)
1154{
1155 krb5_error_code ret;
1156 void *buf = NULL;
1157 size_t len = 0, size = 0;
1158 krb5_enctype enctype;
1159 int pa_type;
1160 hx509_cert kdc_cert = NULL;
1161 size_t i;
1162
1163 if (!config->enable_pkinit) {
1164 krb5_clear_error_message(context);
1165 return 0;
1166 }
1167
1168 if (req->req_body.etype.len > 0) {
1169 for (i = 0; i < req->req_body.etype.len; i++)
1170 if (krb5_enctype_valid(context, req->req_body.etype.val[i]) == 0)
1171 break;
1172 if (req->req_body.etype.len <= i) {
1173 ret = KRB5KRB_ERR_GENERIC;
1174 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret,
1175 "No valid enctype available from client");
1176 goto out;
1177 }
1178 enctype = req->req_body.etype.val[i];
1179 } else
1180 enctype = ETYPE_DES3_CBC_SHA1;
1181
1182 if (cp->type == PKINIT_27) {
1183 PA_PK_AS_REP rep;
1184 const char *type, *other = "";
1185
1186 memset(&rep, 0, sizeof(rep));
1187
1188 pa_type = KRB5_PADATA_PK_AS_REP;
1189
1190 if (cp->keyex == USE_RSA) {
1191 ContentInfo info;
1192
1193 type = "enckey";
1194
1195 rep.element = choice_PA_PK_AS_REP_encKeyPack;
1196
1197 ret = krb5_generate_random_keyblock(context, enctype,
1198 &cp->reply_key);
1199 if (ret) {
1200 free_PA_PK_AS_REP(&rep);
1201 goto out;
1202 }
1203 ret = pk_mk_pa_reply_enckey(context,
1204 config,
1205 cp,
1206 req,
1207 req_buffer,
1208 &cp->reply_key,
1209 &info,
1210 &kdc_cert);
1211 if (ret) {
1212 free_PA_PK_AS_REP(&rep);
1213 goto out;
1214 }
1215 ASN1_MALLOC_ENCODE(ContentInfo, rep.u.encKeyPack.data,
1216 rep.u.encKeyPack.length, &info, &size,
1217 ret);
1218 free_ContentInfo(&info);
1219 if (ret) {
1220 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret, "encoding of Key ContentInfo "
1221 "failed %d", ret);
1222 free_PA_PK_AS_REP(&rep);
1223 goto out;
1224 }
1225 if (rep.u.encKeyPack.length != size)
1226 krb5_abortx(context, "Internal ASN.1 encoder error");
1227
1228 ret = krb5_generate_random_keyblock(context, sessionetype,
1229 sessionkey);
1230 if (ret) {
1231 free_PA_PK_AS_REP(&rep);
1232 goto out;
1233 }
1234
1235 } else {
1236 ContentInfo info;
1237
1238 switch (cp->keyex) {
1239 case USE_DH: type = "dh"; break;
1240 case USE_ECDH: type = "ecdh"; break;
1241 default: krb5_abortx(context, "unknown keyex"); break;
1242 }
1243
1244 if (cp->dh_group_name)
1245 other = cp->dh_group_name;
1246
1247 rep.element = choice_PA_PK_AS_REP_dhInfo;
1248
1249 ret = generate_dh_keyblock(context, cp, enctype);
1250 if (ret)
1251 return ret;
1252
1253 ret = pk_mk_pa_reply_dh(context, config,
1254 cp,
1255 &info,
1256 &kdc_cert);
1257 if (ret) {
1258 free_PA_PK_AS_REP(&rep);
1259 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret,
1260 "create pa-reply-dh "
1261 "failed %d", ret);
1262 goto out;
1263 }
1264
1265 ASN1_MALLOC_ENCODE(ContentInfo, rep.u.dhInfo.dhSignedData.data,
1266 rep.u.dhInfo.dhSignedData.length, &info, &size,
1267 ret);
1268 free_ContentInfo(&info);
1269 if (ret) {
1270 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret,
1271 "encoding of Key ContentInfo "
1272 "failed %d", ret);
1273 free_PA_PK_AS_REP(&rep);
1274 goto out;
1275 }
1276 if (rep.u.encKeyPack.length != size)
1277 krb5_abortx(context, "Internal ASN.1 encoder error");
1278
1279 /* generate the session key using the method from RFC6112 */
1280 {
1281 krb5_keyblock kdc_contribution_key;
1282 krb5_crypto reply_crypto;
1283 krb5_crypto kdccont_crypto;
1284 krb5_data p1 = { strlen("PKINIT"), "PKINIT"};
1285 krb5_data p2 = { strlen("KEYEXCHANGE"), "KEYEXCHANGE"};
1286 void *kckdata;
1287 size_t kcklen;
1288 EncryptedData kx;
1289 void *kxdata;
1290 size_t kxlen;
1291
1292 ret = krb5_generate_random_keyblock(context, sessionetype,
1293 &kdc_contribution_key);
1294 if (ret) {
1295 free_PA_PK_AS_REP(&rep);
1296 goto out;
1297 }
1298 ret = krb5_crypto_init(context, &cp->reply_key, enctype, &reply_crypto);
1299 if (ret) {
1300 krb5_free_keyblock_contents(context, &kdc_contribution_key);
1301 free_PA_PK_AS_REP(&rep);
1302 goto out;
1303 }
1304 ret = krb5_crypto_init(context, &kdc_contribution_key, sessionetype, &kdccont_crypto);
1305 if (ret) {
1306 krb5_crypto_destroy(context, reply_crypto);
1307 krb5_free_keyblock_contents(context, &kdc_contribution_key);
1308 free_PA_PK_AS_REP(&rep);
1309 goto out;
1310 }
1311 /* KRB-FX-CF2 */
1312 ret = krb5_crypto_fx_cf2(context, kdccont_crypto, reply_crypto,
1313 &p1, &p2, sessionetype, sessionkey);
1314 krb5_crypto_destroy(context, kdccont_crypto);
1315 if (ret) {
1316 krb5_crypto_destroy(context, reply_crypto);
1317 krb5_free_keyblock_contents(context, &kdc_contribution_key);
1318 free_PA_PK_AS_REP(&rep);
1319 goto out;
1320 }
1321 ASN1_MALLOC_ENCODE(EncryptionKey, kckdata, kcklen,
1322 &kdc_contribution_key, &size, ret);
1323 krb5_free_keyblock_contents(context, &kdc_contribution_key);
1324 if (ret) {
1325 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret, "encoding of PKINIT-KX Key failed %d", ret);
1326 krb5_crypto_destroy(context, reply_crypto);
1327 free_PA_PK_AS_REP(&rep);
1328 goto out;
1329 }
1330 if (kcklen != size)
1331 krb5_abortx(context, "Internal ASN.1 encoder error");
1332 ret = krb5_encrypt_EncryptedData(context, reply_crypto, KRB5_KU_PA_PKINIT_KX,
1333 kckdata, kcklen, 0, &kx);
1334 krb5_crypto_destroy(context, reply_crypto);
1335 free(kckdata);
1336 if (ret) {
1337 free_PA_PK_AS_REP(&rep);
1338 goto out;
1339 }
1340 ASN1_MALLOC_ENCODE(EncryptedData, kxdata, kxlen,
1341 &kx, &size, ret);
1342 free_EncryptedData(&kx);
1343 if (ret) {
1344 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret, "encoding of PKINIT-KX failed %d", ret);
1345 free_PA_PK_AS_REP(&rep);
1346 goto out;
1347 }
1348 if (kxlen != size)
1349 krb5_abortx(context, "Internal ASN.1 encoder error");
1350 /* Add PA-PKINIT-KX */
1351 ret = krb5_padata_add(context, md, KRB5_PADATA_PKINIT_KX, kxdata, kxlen);
1352 if (ret) {
1353 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret,
1354 "Failed adding PKINIT-KX %d", ret);
1355 free(buf);
1356 goto out;
1357 }
1358 }
1359 }
1360
1361#define use_btmm_with_enckey 0
1362 if (use_btmm_with_enckey && rep.element == choice_PA_PK_AS_REP_encKeyPack) {
1363 PA_PK_AS_REP_BTMM btmm;
1364 heim_any any;
1365
1366 any.data = rep.u.encKeyPack.data;
1367 any.length = rep.u.encKeyPack.length;
1368
1369 btmm.dhSignedData = NULL;
1370 btmm.encKeyPack = &any;
1371
1372 ASN1_MALLOC_ENCODE(PA_PK_AS_REP_BTMM, buf, len, &btmm, &size, ret);
1373 } else {
1374 ASN1_MALLOC_ENCODE(PA_PK_AS_REP, buf, len, &rep, &size, ret);
1375 }
1376
1377 free_PA_PK_AS_REP(&rep);
1378 if (ret) {
1379 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret,
1380 "encode PA-PK-AS-REP failed %d", ret);
1381 goto out;
1382 }
1383 if (len != size)
1384 krb5_abortx(context, "Internal ASN.1 encoder error");
1385
1386 kdc_log(context, config, 0, "PK-INIT using %s %s", type, other);
1387
1388 } else if (cp->type == PKINIT_WIN2K) {
1389 PA_PK_AS_REP_Win2k rep;
1390 ContentInfo info;
1391
1392 if (cp->keyex != USE_RSA) {
1393 ret = KRB5KRB_ERR_GENERIC;
1394 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret,
1395 "Windows PK-INIT doesn't support DH");
1396 goto out;
1397 }
1398
1399 memset(&rep, 0, sizeof(rep));
1400
1401 pa_type = KRB5_PADATA_PK_AS_REP_19;
1402 rep.element = choice_PA_PK_AS_REP_Win2k_encKeyPack;
1403
1404 ret = krb5_generate_random_keyblock(context, enctype,
1405 &cp->reply_key);
1406 if (ret) {
1407 free_PA_PK_AS_REP_Win2k(&rep);
1408 goto out;
1409 }
1410 ret = pk_mk_pa_reply_enckey(context,
1411 config,
1412 cp,
1413 req,
1414 req_buffer,
1415 &cp->reply_key,
1416 &info,
1417 &kdc_cert);
1418 if (ret) {
1419 free_PA_PK_AS_REP_Win2k(&rep);
1420 goto out;
1421 }
1422 ASN1_MALLOC_ENCODE(ContentInfo, rep.u.encKeyPack.data,
1423 rep.u.encKeyPack.length, &info, &size,
1424 ret);
1425 free_ContentInfo(&info);
1426 if (ret) {
1427 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret, "encoding of Key ContentInfo "
1428 "failed %d", ret);
1429 free_PA_PK_AS_REP_Win2k(&rep);
1430 goto out;
1431 }
1432 if (rep.u.encKeyPack.length != size)
1433 krb5_abortx(context, "Internal ASN.1 encoder error");
1434
1435 ASN1_MALLOC_ENCODE(PA_PK_AS_REP_Win2k, buf, len, &rep, &size, ret);
1436 free_PA_PK_AS_REP_Win2k(&rep);
1437 if (ret) {
1438 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret,
1439 "encode PA-PK-AS-REP-Win2k failed %d", ret);
1440 goto out;
1441 }
1442 if (len != size)
1443 krb5_abortx(context, "Internal ASN.1 encoder error");
1444
1445 ret = krb5_generate_random_keyblock(context, sessionetype,
1446 sessionkey);
1447 if (ret) {
1448 free(buf);
1449 goto out;
1450 }
1451
1452 } else
1453 krb5_abortx(context, "PK-INIT internal error");
1454
1455
1456 ret = krb5_padata_add(context, md, pa_type, buf, len);
1457 if (ret) {
1458 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret,
1459 "Failed adding PA-PK-AS-REP %d", ret);
1460 free(buf);
1461 goto out;
1462 }
1463
1464 if (config->pkinit_kdc_ocsp_file) {
1465
1466 if (ocsp.expire == 0 && ocsp.next_update > kdc_time) {
1467 struct stat sb;
1468 int fd;
1469
1470 krb5_data_free(&ocsp.data);
1471
1472 ocsp.expire = 0;
1473 ocsp.next_update = kdc_time + 60 * 5;
1474
1475 fd = open(config->pkinit_kdc_ocsp_file, O_RDONLY);
1476 if (fd < 0) {
1477 kdc_log(context, config, 0,
1478 "PK-INIT failed to open ocsp data file %d", errno);
1479 goto out_ocsp;
1480 }
1481 ret = fstat(fd, &sb);
1482 if (ret) {
1483 ret = errno;
1484 close(fd);
1485 kdc_log(context, config, 0,
1486 "PK-INIT failed to stat ocsp data %d", ret);
1487 goto out_ocsp;
1488 }
1489
1490 ret = krb5_data_alloc(&ocsp.data, sb.st_size);
1491 if (ret) {
1492 close(fd);
1493 kdc_log(context, config, 0,
1494 "PK-INIT failed to stat ocsp data %d", ret);
1495 goto out_ocsp;
1496 }
1497 ocsp.data.length = sb.st_size;
1498 ret = read(fd, ocsp.data.data, sb.st_size);
1499 close(fd);
1500 if (ret != sb.st_size) {
1501 kdc_log(context, config, 0,
1502 "PK-INIT failed to read ocsp data %d", errno);
1503 goto out_ocsp;
1504 }
1505
1506 ret = hx509_ocsp_verify(context->hx509ctx,
1507 kdc_time,
1508 kdc_cert,
1509 0,
1510 ocsp.data.data, ocsp.data.length,
1511 &ocsp.expire);
1512 if (ret) {
1513 kdc_log(context, config, 0,
1514 "PK-INIT failed to verify ocsp data %d", ret);
1515 krb5_data_free(&ocsp.data);
1516 ocsp.expire = 0;
1517 } else if (ocsp.expire > 180) {
1518 ocsp.expire -= 180; /* refetch the ocsp before it expire */
1519 ocsp.next_update = ocsp.expire;
1520 } else {
1521 ocsp.next_update = kdc_time;
1522 }
1523 out_ocsp:
1524 ret = 0;
1525 }
1526
1527 if (ocsp.expire != 0 && ocsp.expire > kdc_time) {
1528
1529 ret = krb5_padata_add(context, md,
1530 KRB5_PADATA_PA_PK_OCSP_RESPONSE,
1531 ocsp.data.data, ocsp.data.length);
1532 if (ret) {
1533 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret,
1534 "Failed adding OCSP response %d", ret);
1535 goto out;
1536 }
1537 }
1538 }
1539
1540out:
1541 if (kdc_cert)
1542 hx509_cert_free(kdc_cert);
1543
1544 if (ret == 0)
1545 ret = krb5_copy_keyblock_contents(context, &cp->reply_key, reply_key);
1546 return ret;
1547}

1549static int
1550match_rfc_san(krb5_context context,
1551 krb5_kdc_configuration *config,
1552 hx509_context hx509ctx,
1553 hx509_cert client_cert,
1554 krb5_const_principal match)
1555{
1556 hx509_octet_string_list list;
1557 int ret, found = 0;
1558 size_t i;
1559
1560 memset(&list, 0 , sizeof(list));
1561
1562 ret = hx509_cert_find_subjectAltName_otherName(hx509ctx,
1563 client_cert,
1564 &asn1_oid_id_pkinit_san,
1565 &list);
1566 if (ret)
1567 goto out;
1568
1569 for (i = 0; !found && i < list.len; i++) {
1570 krb5_principal_data principal;
1571 KRB5PrincipalName kn;
1572 size_t size;
1573
1574 ret = decode_KRB5PrincipalName(list.val[i].data,
1575 list.val[i].length,
1576 &kn, &size);
1577 if (ret) {
1578 const char *msg = krb5_get_error_message(context, ret);
1579 kdc_log(context, config, 0,
1580 "Decoding kerberos name in certificate failed: %s", msg);
1581 krb5_free_error_message(context, msg);
1582 break;
1583 }
1584 if (size != list.val[i].length) {
1585 kdc_log(context, config, 0,
1586 "Decoding kerberos name have extra bits on the end");
1587 return KRB5_KDC_ERR_CLIENT_NAME_MISMATCH;
1588 }
1589
1590 memset(&principal, 0, sizeof (principal));
1591 principal.name = kn.principalName;
1592 principal.realm = kn.realm;
1593
1594 if (krb5_principal_compare(context, &principal, match) == TRUE)
1595 found = 1;
1596 free_KRB5PrincipalName(&kn);
1597 }
1598
1599out:
1600 hx509_free_octet_string_list(&list);
1601 if (ret)
1602 return ret;
1603
1604 if (!found)
1605 return KRB5_KDC_ERR_CLIENT_NAME_MISMATCH;
1606
1607 return 0;
1608}

1610static int
1611match_ms_upn_san(krb5_context context,
1612 krb5_kdc_configuration *config,
1613 hx509_context hx509ctx,
1614 hx509_cert client_cert,
1615 HDB *clientdb,
1616 hdb_entry_ex *client)
1617{
1618 hx509_octet_string_list list;
1619 krb5_principal principal = NULL;
1620 int ret;
1621 MS_UPN_SAN upn;
1622 size_t size;
1623
1624 memset(&list, 0 , sizeof(list));
1625
1626 ret = hx509_cert_find_subjectAltName_otherName(hx509ctx,
1627 client_cert,
1628 &asn1_oid_id_pkinit_ms_san,
1629 &list);
1630 if (ret)
1631 goto out;
1632
1633 if (list.len != 1) {
1634 kdc_log(context, config, 0,
1635 "More then one PK-INIT MS UPN SAN");
1636 ret = KRB5_KDC_ERR_CLIENT_NAME_MISMATCH;
1637 goto out;
1638 }
1639
1640 ret = decode_MS_UPN_SAN(list.val[0].data, list.val[0].length, &upn, &size);
1641 if (ret) {
1642 kdc_log(context, config, 0, "Decode of MS-UPN-SAN failed");
1643 goto out;
1644 }
1645 if (size != list.val[0].length) {
1646 free_MS_UPN_SAN(&upn);
1647 kdc_log(context, config, 0, "Trailing data in ");
1648 ret = KRB5_KDC_ERR_CLIENT_NAME_MISMATCH;
1649 goto out;
1650 }
1651
1652 kdc_log(context, config, 0, "found MS UPN SAN: %s", upn);
1653
1654 ret = krb5_parse_name(context, upn, &principal);
1655 free_MS_UPN_SAN(&upn);
1656 if (ret) {
1657 kdc_log(context, config, 0, "Failed to parse principal in MS UPN SAN");
1658 goto out;
1659 }
1660
1661 if (clientdb->hdb_check_pkinit_ms_upn_match) {
1662 ret = clientdb->hdb_check_pkinit_ms_upn_match(context, clientdb, client, principal);
1663 } else {
1664
1665 /*
1666 * This is very wrong, but will do for a fallback
1667 */
1668 strupr(principal->realm);
1669
1670 if (krb5_principal_compare(context, principal, client->entry.principal) == FALSE)
1671 ret = KRB5_KDC_ERR_CLIENT_NAME_MISMATCH;
1672 }
1673
1674out:
1675 if (principal)
1676 krb5_free_principal(context, principal);
1677 hx509_free_octet_string_list(&list);
1678
1679 return ret;
1680}

1682krb5_error_code
1683_kdc_pk_check_client(krb5_context context,
1684 krb5_kdc_configuration *config,
1685 HDB *clientdb,
1686 hdb_entry_ex *client,
1687 pk_client_params *cp,
1688 char **subject_name)
1689{
1690 const HDB_Ext_PKINIT_acl *acl;
1691 const HDB_Ext_PKINIT_cert *pc;
1692 krb5_error_code ret;
1693 hx509_name name;
1694 size_t i;
1695
1696 if (cp->cert == NULL) {
1697
1698 *subject_name = strdup("anonymous client client");
1699 if (*subject_name == NULL)
1700 return ENOMEM;
1701 return 0;
1702 }
1703
1704 ret = hx509_cert_get_base_subject(context->hx509ctx,
1705 cp->cert,
1706 &name);
1707 if (ret)
1708 return ret;
1709
1710 ret = hx509_name_to_string(name, subject_name);
1711 hx509_name_free(&name);
1712 if (ret)
1713 return ret;
1714
1715 kdc_log(context, config, 0,
1716 "Trying to authorize PK-INIT subject DN %s",
1717 *subject_name);
1718
1719 ret = hdb_entry_get_pkinit_cert(&client->entry, &pc);
1720 if (ret == 0 && pc) {
1721 hx509_cert cert;
1722 size_t j;
1723
1724 for (j = 0; j < pc->len; j++) {
1725 cert = hx509_cert_init_data(context->hx509ctx,
1726 pc->val[j].cert.data,
1727 pc->val[j].cert.length,
1728 NULL);
1729 if (cert == NULL)
1730 continue;
1731 ret = hx509_cert_cmp(cert, cp->cert);
1732 hx509_cert_free(cert);
1733 if (ret == 0) {
1734 kdc_log(context, config, 5,
1735 "Found matching PK-INIT cert in hdb");
1736 return 0;
1737 }
1738 }
1739 }
1740
1741
1742 if (config->pkinit_princ_in_cert) {
1743 ret = match_rfc_san(context, config,
1744 context->hx509ctx,
1745 cp->cert,
1746 client->entry.principal);
1747 if (ret == 0) {
1748 kdc_log(context, config, 5,
1749 "Found matching PK-INIT SAN in certificate");
1750 return 0;
1751 }
1752 ret = match_ms_upn_san(context, config,
1753 context->hx509ctx,
1754 cp->cert,
1755 clientdb,
1756 client);
1757 if (ret == 0) {
1758 kdc_log(context, config, 5,
1759 "Found matching MS UPN SAN in certificate");
1760 return 0;
1761 }
1762 }
1763
1764 ret = hdb_entry_get_pkinit_acl(&client->entry, &acl);
1765 if (ret == 0 && acl != NULL) {
1766 /*
1767 * Cheat here and compare the generated name with the string
1768 * and not the reverse.
1769 */
1770 for (i = 0; i < acl->len; i++) {
1771 if (strcmp(*subject_name, acl->val[0].subject) != 0)
1772 continue;
1773
1774 /* Don't support isser and anchor checking right now */
1775 if (acl->val[0].issuer)
1776 continue;
1777 if (acl->val[0].anchor)
1778 continue;
1779
1780 kdc_log(context, config, 5,
1781 "Found matching PK-INIT database ACL");
1782 return 0;
1783 }
1784 }
1785
1786 for (i = 0; i < principal_mappings.len; i++) {
1787 krb5_boolean b;
1788
1789 b = krb5_principal_compare(context,
1790 client->entry.principal,
1791 principal_mappings.val[i].principal);
1792 if (b == FALSE)
1793 continue;
1794 if (strcmp(principal_mappings.val[i].subject, *subject_name) != 0)
1795 continue;
1796 kdc_log(context, config, 5,
1797 "Found matching PK-INIT FILE ACL");
1798 return 0;
1799 }
1800
1801 ret = KRB5_KDC_ERR_CLIENT_NAME_MISMATCH;
1802 krb5_set_error_message(context, ret,
1803 "PKINIT no matching principals for %s",
1804 *subject_name);
1805
1806 kdc_log(context, config, 5,
1807 "PKINIT no matching principals for %s",
1808 *subject_name);
1809
1810 free(*subject_name);
1811 *subject_name = NULL;
1812
1813 return ret;
1814}

1816static krb5_error_code
1817add_principal_mapping(krb5_context context,
1818 const char *principal_name,
1819 const char * subject)
1820{
1821 struct pk_allowed_princ *tmp;
1822 krb5_principal principal;
1823 krb5_error_code ret;
1824
1825 tmp = realloc(principal_mappings.val,
1826 (principal_mappings.len + 1) * sizeof(*tmp));
1827 if (tmp == NULL)
1828 return ENOMEM;
1829 principal_mappings.val = tmp;
1830
1831 ret = krb5_parse_name(context, principal_name, &principal);
1832 if (ret)
1833 return ret;
1834
1835 principal_mappings.val[principal_mappings.len].principal = principal;
1836
1837 principal_mappings.val[principal_mappings.len].subject = strdup(subject);
1838 if (principal_mappings.val[principal_mappings.len].subject == NULL) {
1839 krb5_free_principal(context, principal);
1840 return ENOMEM;
1841 }
1842 principal_mappings.len++;
1843
1844 return 0;
1845}

1879
1880static void
1881load_mappings(krb5_context context, const char *fn)
1882{
1883 krb5_error_code ret;
1884 char buf[1024];
1885 unsigned long lineno = 0;
1886 FILE *f;
1887
1888 f = fopen(fn, "r");
1889 if (f == NULL)
1890 return;
1891
1892 while (fgets(buf, sizeof(buf), f) != NULL) {
1893 char *subject_name, *p;
1894
1895 buf[strcspn(buf, "\n")] = '\0';
1896 lineno++;
1897
1898 p = buf + strspn(buf, " \t");
1899
1900 if (*p == '#' || *p == '\0')
1901 continue;
1902
1903 subject_name = strchr(p, ':');
1904 if (subject_name == NULL) {
1905 krb5_warnx(context, "pkinit mapping file line %lu "
1906 "missing \":\" :%s",
1907 lineno, buf);
1908 continue;
1909 }
1910 *subject_name++ = '\0';
1911
1912 ret = add_principal_mapping(context, p, subject_name);
1913 if (ret) {
1914 krb5_warn(context, ret, "failed to add line %lu \":\" :%s\n",
1915 lineno, buf);
1916 continue;
1917 }
1918 }
1919
1920 fclose(f);
1921}

1926
1927krb5_error_code
1928krb5_kdc_pk_initialize(krb5_context context,
1929 krb5_kdc_configuration *config,
1930 const char *user_id,
1931 const char *anchors,
1932 char **pool,
1933 char **revoke_list)
1934{
1935 const char *file;
1936 char *fn = NULL;
1937 krb5_error_code ret;
1938
1939 file = krb5_config_get_string(context, NULL,
1940 "libdefaults", "moduli", NULL);
1941
1942 ret = _krb5_parse_moduli(context, file, &moduli);
1943 if (ret)
1944 krb5_err(context, 1, ret, "PKINIT: failed to load modidi file");
1945
1946 principal_mappings.len = 0;
1947 principal_mappings.val = NULL;
1948
1949 ret = _krb5_pk_load_id(context,
1950 &kdc_identity,
1951 user_id,
1952 anchors,
1953 pool,
1954 revoke_list,
1955 NULL,
1956 NULL,
1957 NULL);
1958 if (ret) {
1959 krb5_warn(context, ret, "PKINIT: ");
1960 config->enable_pkinit = 0;
1961 return ret;
1962 }
1963
1964 {
1965 hx509_query *q;
1966 hx509_cert cert;
1967
1968 ret = hx509_query_alloc(context->hx509ctx, &q);
1969 if (ret) {
1970 krb5_warnx(context, "PKINIT: out of memory");
1971 return ENOMEM;
1972 }
1973
1974 hx509_query_match_option(q, HX509_QUERY_OPTION_PRIVATE_KEY);
1975 if (config->pkinit_kdc_friendly_name)
1976 hx509_query_match_friendly_name(q, config->pkinit_kdc_friendly_name);
1977
1978 ret = hx509_certs_find(context->hx509ctx,
1979 kdc_identity->certs,
1980 q,
1981 &cert);
1982 hx509_query_free(context->hx509ctx, q);
1983 if (ret == 0) {
1984 if (hx509_cert_check_eku(context->hx509ctx, cert,
1985 &asn1_oid_id_pkkdcekuoid, 0)) {
1986 hx509_name name;
1987 char *str;
1988 ret = hx509_cert_get_subject(cert, &name);
1989 if (ret == 0) {
1990 hx509_name_to_string(name, &str);
1991 krb5_warnx(context, "WARNING Found KDC certificate (%s)"
1992 "is missing the PK-INIT KDC EKU, this is bad for "
1993 "interoperability.", str);
1994 hx509_name_free(&name);
1995 free(str);
1996 }
1997 }
1998 hx509_cert_free(cert);
1999 } else
2000 krb5_warnx(context, "PKINIT: failed to find a signing "
2001 "certifiate with a public key");
2002 }
2003
2004 if (krb5_config_get_bool_default(context,
2005 NULL,
2006 FALSE,
2007 "kdc",
2008 "pkinit_allow_proxy_certificate",
2009 NULL))
2010 config->pkinit_allow_proxy_certs = 1;
2011
2012 file = krb5_config_get_string(context,
2013 NULL,
2014 "kdc",
2015 "pkinit_mappings_file",
2016 NULL);
2017 if (file == NULL) {
2018 int aret;
2019
2020 aret = asprintf(&fn, "%s/pki-mapping", hdb_db_dir(context));
2021 if (aret == -1) {
2022 krb5_warnx(context, "PKINIT: out of memory");
2023 return ENOMEM;
2024 }
2025
2026 file = fn;
2027 }
2028
2029 load_mappings(context, file);
2030 if (fn)
2031 free(fn);
2032
2033 return 0;
2034}
